The paper discusses the expressiveness of communicating ASP, which is a form of declarative programming used for solving complex problems. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions PSPACE-complete problems such as STRIPS planning, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of computing answer sets, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
